title: EPL MW26: Brentford vs Arsenal?
question: EPL MW26: Brentford vs Arsenal?
description:
## Resolution Criteria
This market will resolve based on the official final score of the match between **Brentford** and **Arsenal**, scheduled for February 12, 2026, including any goals scored in extra time and the outcome of a penalty shootout, as recorded by the competition organiser.
###
*Postponement Policy: If the match is postponed to a date more than 48 hours after the original kickoff time, the market will resolve as "N/A".*
###
*Abandonment: If the match starts but is abandoned and not completed within 48 hours, the market will resolve according to the status of the match at the time of abandonment if an official result is declared, otherwise it will resolve as "N/A".*
###
*Full-time policy: Extra time and penalty shootouts (if played) are included for resolution.*

## Resolution Source
[Official Premier League website](https://www.premierleague.com/en)

[Official Matchweek Schedule](https://www.premierleague.com/en/matches?competition=8&season=2025&matchweek=26&month=01)

## Additional Information
*This market will end before the match begins, and will be resolved within 24 hours after the official score announcement.*

title: Bank of Japan decision in March 2026?
question: Bank of Japan decision in March 2026?
description:
### Resolution Criteria
This market will resolve to the amount of basis points the upper bound of the short-term policy interest rate is changed by versus the level it was prior to the Bank of Japan's **March 2026** meeting.

If the short-term policy interest rate is changed to a level not expressed in the displayed options, the change will be rounded up to the nearest 25 and will resolve to the relevant bracket (e.g. if there's a cut/increase of 12.5 bps it will be considered to be 25 bps).

This market may resolve as soon as the Bank of Japan's statement for their **March** meeting with relevant data is issued. If no statement is released by the end date of this meeting, this market will resolve to the "No Change" bracket.

### Resolution Source
The resolution source for this market is the Bank of Japan's statement after its meeting scheduled for **March 18 - 19, 2026** according to the [official calendar](https://www.boj.or.jp/en/mopo/mpmsche_minu/index.htm).

The level and change of the target short-term policy interest rate is also published at the [official website of the Bank of Japan](https://www.boj.or.jp/en/mopo/mpmdeci/state_2025/index.htm).


## Additional Information
*This market will end before the Bank of Japan meeting begins, and it will resolve within 24 hours of the statement release.*
